</taxonomicName>
Complex
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,222,462]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
Two species comprise the 
<taxonomicName box="[448,534,222,246]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delvasi">
<emphasis box="[448,534,222,246]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Delvasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Complex: 
<taxonomicName authority="Delgado &amp; Collantes 1996" authorityName="Delgado &amp; Collantes" authorityYear="1996" box="[667,1093,222,247]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delvasi">
<emphasis box="[667,781,222,247]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">H. delvasi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Delgado" box="[788,1093,222,246]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refString="Delgado, J. A. &amp; Collantes, F. (1996). A new species of water beetle, Hydraena delvasi, from Colombia, South America (Coleoptera: Hydraenidae). Studies on Neotropical Fauna &amp; Environment 31, 54 - 56." type="journal article" year="1996">
Delgado &amp; Collantes 
<number box="[1034,1093,222,246]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[1152,1269,222,247]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stellula">
<emphasis box="[1152,1269,222,247]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">H. stellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1285,1379,222,246]" captionStart="FIGURE 96" captionStartId="138.[151,250,1650,1673]" captionTargetBox="[249,1335,193,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@138.[249,1338,193,1629]" captionTargetPageId="138" captionText="FIGURE 96. Hydraena delvasi, holotype, dorsal and lateral habitus, and venter." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050164/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Figs. 96</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1391,1422,222,246]" captionStart="FIGURE 97" captionStartId="139.[151,250,1650,1673]" captionTargetBox="[263,1321,193,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@139.[263,1323,193,1629]" captionTargetPageId="139" captionText="FIGURE 97. Hydraena stellula, holotype, dorsal and lateral habitus, and venter." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1050168/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">97</figureCitation>
). These are small to medium sized species (ca. 
<quantity box="[659,826,258,282]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.325" metricValueMax="1.42" metricValueMin="1.23" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="1.325" valueMax="1.42" valueMin="1.23">1.23–1.42 mm</quantity>
), which have the pronotum with a more or less distinct dark fascia or macula. The species differ somewhat in dorsal habitus, and are considered to be related because of the aedeagal form: the distal part of the aedeagus has 
<number box="[770,811,330,354]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
lobes, the dorsal surface of the main piece has spinose projections, and the parameres are very short, originating on the ventral face of the main piece, near the distal part of the aedeagus. The currently known species are from 
<collectingCountry box="[767,877,402,426]" name="Colombia" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[931,1046,402,426]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venezuela">
<collectingCountry box="[931,1046,402,426]" name="Venezuela" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1062,1175,403,427]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delvasi">
<emphasis box="[1062,1175,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">H. delvasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<collectingCountry box="[1245,1338,402,426]" name="Ecuador" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stellula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">H. stellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
